    "clinical_summary": "A 58-year-old female, 14 days post-ORIF for right tibial plateau fracture, demonstrates toe-touch weight-bearing compliance on the operative limb with a peak right-sided force of 268.6 N (approximately 33.4% body weight), which exceeds the prescribed 20% BW restriction (~160 N). Gait timing is symmetric and cadence is within a functional range, but a significant force asymmetry (SI=32.1%) reflects appropriate offloading strategy; however, the absolute right-limb load remains a clinical safety concern requiring immediate attention.",
