      "notes": "Patient body weight is 82 kg (804 N). The prescribed toe-touch WB limit of 20% BW equates to approximately 160.8 N. The recorded maximum right-limb force is 268.6 N (~33.4% BW) and the average peak right force is 261.1 N (~32.5% BW), both exceeding the restriction by approximately 60-65%. This is a meaningful over-loading event at only 14 days post-ORIF of a tibial plateau fracture with locking plate fixation. Implant and fracture site integrity may be at risk with sustained loads of this magnitude at this stage of healing."
