      "timing_symmetry_notes": "Timing symmetry index of 0.0% indicates perfectly matched stride durations bilaterally (both 1.0 s average), suggesting the patient has established a stable, rhythmically coordinated gait pattern. Stance phase asymmetry index of 6.7% is mild; right stance is shorter (74.6%) than left (79.7%), consistent with guarding of the operative limb.",
      "clinical_significance": "The combination of normal timing symmetry with significant force asymmetry is a classic compensatory pattern in restricted weight-bearing gait. The shorter right stance phase and reduced right peak force represent active protective strategy, but force loading still exceeds protocol limits."
